This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) because it presents a learned model for computing the similarity of two strings, which is a common task in NLP. The use of a convolutional neural network also suggests a focus on deep learning techniques, which is a common approach in NLP research. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV) due to the use of learned representations and alignment techniques that are relevant to these fields.
